<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[198,878,650,676]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,549,650,676]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Diagnosis. Imago (external).</emphasis>
Wingspan: 
<quantity box="[690,794,650,676]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="13.5">13.5 mm</quantity>
(apo.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Head, patagia, anterior part of tegulae, prothorax, basal part of costa, triangular patch of medial area, and terminal area, including fringes: black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[197,1086,770,796]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Forewing: long and narrow, with pointed apex; brown ground colour (apo.).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[197,851,810,836]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Abdomen: dark grey; with dorsal tuft on basal segment.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Crosslines: untraceable, except subterminal line weakly marked, beige, and terminal line marked by black interneural dots.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[197,744,930,956]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Reniform stigma: beige, ovoid, black outlined.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Hindwing: grey; with narrow brown terminal line and indistinct discal spot; fringes basally beige, distally grey.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[197,1033,1050,1076]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Underside: forewing grey-brown; hindwing light grey, with discal spot.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[198,1342,1090,1116]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,384,1090,1116]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Tegumen-fultura superior: fused, with diaphragm medially forming a tube (apo.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[197,1161,1130,1156]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Vinculum: two-branched; centre one barlike; posterior one branchlike, not curved.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[197,696,1170,1196]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Saccus: relatively long; broadly U-shaped.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[197,553,1210,1236]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Valvae: slightly asymmetrical.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Ampulla: bilobed; slightly asymmetrical; lobes tapered strongly from subapically twice as broad and rounded ventral part to slightly shorter dorsal, rounded tip; dorsal lobe narrow, straight; ventral lobe broad, curved (apo.)</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[197,820,1370,1396]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Digitus: rather large, platelike, broadly quadrangular.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Juxta-anellus plate: inseparable (phallus on left side); base strongly asymmetrical, with narrow processes; medially with extremely long, heavily sclerotised, free, tapered, and S-curved process; with curved, setose, pointed tip (apo.).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Phallus: coecum short and broad, smoothly rounded; broadest by ductus ejaculatorius; there with short forewardly directed process (a stop-function connected with juxta-anellus ventral processes); slightly upturned and tapered outwards; tip ventrally with small hook (apo.).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[197,1149,1650,1676]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Vesica: armed with a small and short, heavily sclerotised rectangular plate (apo.).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[198,1024,1690,1716]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,473,1690,1716]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[480,600,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">F. s-forma</emphasis>
differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[822,986,1690,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Fustis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[822,893,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fustis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[198,518,1730,1756]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">- brown ground colour;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[198,698,1770,1796]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">- fused tegumen-fultura superior plate;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[198,400,1810,1836]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">male genitalia, in</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[198,824,1850,1876]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">- shape of ampulla, especially narrow dorsal arm;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[198,727,1890,1916]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">- long, S-formed, setose, pointed anellus;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,530,1956]" box="[198,1044,1930,1956]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">- phallus short, slightly upturned, with ventral small hook at tip; and</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
